This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as entity linking and relation extraction, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed model is a neural network, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is trained using machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of distant supervision, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to solving these tasks, which could be of interest to researchers in the subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE).
